---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const GITHUB_URL = 'https://github.com/thatcube/Plozz';
const SPONSOR_URL = 'https://github.com/sponsors/thatcube';
const CONTACT_EMAIL = 'feedback@plozz.app';
const SENTRY_PRIVACY_URL = 'https://sentry.io/privacy/';
const GITHUB_PRIVACY_URL = 'https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement';
const LAST_UPDATED = 'July 1, 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — Plozz"
  description="Plozz takes a minimal-data approach: by default it collects nothing, stores your server credentials only on your device, and connects directly to the Jellyfin or Plex servers you choose. Crash reporting is optional and off by default."
>
  <main class="legal">
    <div class="container">
      <a class="legal-home" href="/">
        <img src="/logo.svg" alt="" width="28" height="28" />
        <span>Plozz</span>
      </a>

      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: {LAST_UPDATED}</p>

      <p>
        Plozz is a client app for connecting to your own Jellyfin and Plex media
        servers. We take a minimal-data approach.
      </p>

      <h2>What we collect</h2>
      <p>
        By default, nothing. Plozz has no analytics or tracking, and out of the
        box it does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data to us or
        any third party. The only information that ever leaves your device is
        what you deliberately choose to send: an optional crash report (off
        unless you turn it on) or a bug report you submit yourself. Both are
        described below.
      </p>

      <h2>Crash reports (optional, off by default)</h2>
      <p>
        Plozz includes an optional crash-reporting feature that is
        <strong>turned off by default</strong>. If you enable it under
        Settings → Help &amp; Diagnostics → Share Crash Reports and the app later
        crashes, freezes, or is shut down by the system, Plozz sends an
        anonymous diagnostic report so the problem can be found and fixed.
      </p>
      <p>
        These reports contain only the technical details of the failure plus
        your app version, tvOS version, and device model (for example
        “Apple TV 4K”). They never include your name, your server addresses,
        your logins or tokens, or anything about what you were watching. Reports
        are processed and stored by our error-monitoring provider,
        <a href={SENTRY_PRIVACY_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener">Sentry</a>
        (Functional Software, Inc.), on servers in the United States, under
        Sentry’s privacy policy. You can turn crash reporting off at any time,
        which stops any further reports.
      </p>

      <h2>Bug reports &amp; feedback</h2>
      <p>
        When you choose to report a problem from inside Plozz, the app shows a
        link and QR code that open a pre-filled issue on our public
        <a href={`${GITHUB_URL}/issues`} target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
        repository — only you decide whether to submit it. The pre-filled text
        includes a small, non-secret summary of your setup (app version, tvOS
        version, device model, and whether you use Jellyfin and/or Plex) and
        never your server addresses, logins, or tokens. Anything you post to
        GitHub is public and handled under
        <a href={GITHUB_PRIVACY_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub’s privacy policy</a>.
        You can also email us at
        <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>; we only receive
        what you choose to send.
      </p>

      <h2>Your server details</h2>
      <p>
        The server addresses and login credentials you enter are stored locally
        on your device (in the system Keychain) and are used only to connect to
        the servers you choose. They are never sent to us.
      </p>

      <h2>Network connections</h2>
      <p>
        Plozz communicates directly with the Jellyfin or Plex servers you
        configure. Any data handling on those servers is governed by their own
        privacy policies and the policies of whoever operates them. The only
        other network destination is our crash-reporting provider, and only if
        you opt in to crash reports (see above).
      </p>

      <h2>Children</h2>
      <p>
        Plozz is not directed at children and does not knowingly collect data
        from anyone.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>We may update this policy; changes will be posted at this URL.</p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>

  <footer class="site-footer">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="footer-brand">
        <img src="/logo.svg" alt="" width="22" height="22" />
        <span>Plozz</span>
      </div>
      <div class="footer-links">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <a href="/privacy">Privacy</a>
        <a href={GITHUB_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
        <a href={SPONSOR_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener">Sponsor</a>
        <a href={`${GITHUB_URL}/issues`} target="_blank" rel="noopener">Support</a>
      </div>
      <div>© {new Date().getFullYear()} Plozz · GPL-3.0</div>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal {
    padding: 64px 0 88px;
  }

  .legal .container {
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .legal-home {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 48px;
    transition: color 0.15s ease;
  }

  .legal-home:hover {
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .legal-home img {
    width: 28px;
    height: 28px;
    image-rendering: pixelated;
  }

  .legal h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 2.8rem);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .legal-updated {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    margin-bottom: 36px;
  }

  .legal h2 {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    margin-top: 36px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .legal p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }

  .legal a {
    color: var(--brand);
  }

  .legal a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
